vinas, Maurice Merleau-Ponty, Jacques Derrida, Ludwig Wittgenstein, Aron Gurwitsch, and Harold Garfinkel—even as these naturally occurring case studies provide fresh specifications for these thinkers' ideas.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCoffee tastingxPhilosophy. 0aObjectivity. 0aSubjectivity. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology of Work. 4aCommunication : Communication. 4aHistory : Social and Cultural History. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848898140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438488981423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438488981/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles